    h2 How We Determine Burn Safety Conditions
    p Outdoor burning is most affected by three key weather and environmental factors:
    table
      tr 
        th Factor
        th Why it Matters
      tr
        td Wind Speed
        td Wind spreads embers, flame, and smoke. High wind = high fire risk.
      tr
        td Humidity
        td Low humidity dries out vegetation, making it extremely flammable.
      tr
        td Local Burn Bans
        td Issued by counties to prevent wildfires during dangerous conditions.
